Re: Checking the block chain on load

Bitcointalk

2010-08-18 18:28:28 UTC - [11]Original Post

   In the next SVN rev, Iʼll make it only go back to the last checkpoint
   at block 74000.  If we need to correct a problem in the future, we can
   always make sure it goes back at least as far back as the problem.
   Also, Iʼm adding code to verify the block index, which means the
   proof-of-work chain is checked.
   Still, the system wonʼt be entirely secure against your blk*.dat
   files.  You are trusting someone if you use a copy of their blk files.
